All Implemented Interfaces:
ICdmBase, IReferencedEntity, ITypeDesignation, Serializable
public class SpecimenTypeDesignation
extends TypeDesignationBase
implements ITypeDesignation

The class representing a typification of one or several taxon names by a specimen or a figure. All taxon names which have a rank "species aggregate" or lower can only be typified by specimens. Moreover each typification by a specimen (or by a figure) has a status like "holotype" or "isotype".

This class corresponds to:

  • NomenclaturalType according to the TDWG ontology
  • Typification (partially) according to the TCS
  • NomenclaturalTypeDesignation according to the ABCD schema

Version:
1.0
Author:
m.doering

Parameters:

status - the type designation status
citation - the reference source for the new designation
citationMicroReference - the string with the details describing the exact localisation within the reference
originalNameString - the taxon name string used originally in the reference source for the new designation
isNotDesignated - the boolean flag indicating whether there is no specimen type at all for this specimen type designation

getTypeStatus

public TypeDesignationStatus getTypeStatus()
Returns the type designation status for this specimen type designation. This status describes which of the possible categories of types like "holotype", "neotype", "syntype" or "isotype" applies to this specimen type designation.

isLectoType

public boolean isLectoType()
Returns the boolean value indicating whether this specimen type designation has a "lectotype" status (true) or not (false).
A lectotype is a specimen or illustration designated as the nomenclatural type, when no holotype was indicated at the time of publication of the "type-bringing" taxon name, when the holotype is found to belong to more than one taxon name, or as long as it is missing.
